text: welcome to let's talk a premie Learning
Center for English communication skills
making you speak fluent English with
neutral accent singular and plural there
are two forms of nouns in the English
language singular and plural singular
denotes one and plural denotes more than
one the plural of a noun is generally
formed by adding an S for example girl
girls some more examples pen pens dog
dogs book books nouns ending with a
letter s SH CH or X form the plural by
adding es to the singular glass glasses
brush brushes dish dishes watch watches
box boxes Fox foxes most of the nouns
ending with O form plurals by adding ES
and few words by adding s to the
singular Buffalo buffalos mango mangoes
some more examples photo photos piano
pianos few nouns form their plurals by
adding en or ar e in to their singular
ox oxen child children nouns ending with
y from their plural by replacing Y with
IES
for example pony ponies butterfly
butterflies cherry cherries as we are
aware there are 26 letters in the
English alphabet series five of which
are vowels and the remaining 21 are
consonants few nouns change their
singular by replacing the inside vowel
to form and plural man men in this case
the vowel a is changed to e in the
plural form some more examples tooth
teeth goose geese in this case the vowel
o o is changed to e e in the plural form
mouse mice in this case the vowel o u is
changed to I in the plural form for
words ending with F E or F have plurals
ending with v e s for example knife
knives wolf wolves shelf shells both
singular and plural are the same for
some nouns for example sheep sheep deer
deer milk milk money money food food
scissors scissors let's find the plural
words for the singular words in this
fruit market brinjal brinjals pumpkin
pumpkins tomato Tomatoes orange oranges
